# Database backups (timestamped). The `*.db` blanket above does NOT match
# `*.db.bak-YYYYMMDD-HHMMSS`. These are local recovery artifacts only —
# always 100MB+, well over GitHub's hard limit, never belong in version control.
data/*.db.bak-*
data/*.db.bak

# Stray top-level diff/patch artifacts left over from ad-hoc work.
# `patch.diff` shows up when someone exports a quick fix to disk and forgets
# to clean up. Never belongs in version control.
/*.diff
/*.patch

.envrc

# graphify outputs — knowledge graph artifacts written by `/graphify <path>` or
# `graphify extract`. Includes graph.json (queryable), graph.html (viz),
# GRAPH_REPORT.md, Obsidian vault, wiki/, cache/ (SHA256 extraction cache). All
# re-derivable from source via `graphify update <path>` (AST-only, free).
# Single full graph can be 50MB+; vault has 100s of files. Never in VCS.
graphify-out/
**/graphify-out/

# V7 build telemetry — intermediate artifacts emitted per module by
# scripts/build/v7_build.py. These are large, machine-regenerated on every
# build, and forbidden in PRs by the AGENTS.md pre-submit checklist
# ("generated artifacts"). Scoped to the curriculum tree so unrelated files
# elsewhere with the same names aren't affected. Added 2026-05-13 after a
# stash containing the dirty post-build tree was dropped and ~30min of
# validated build output was lost — recurrence prevention.
curriculum/l2-uk-en/*/*/python_qg.json
curriculum/l2-uk-en/*/*/wiki_manifest.json
curriculum/l2-uk-en/*/*/writer_output.raw.md
curriculum/l2-uk-en/*/*/writer_tool_calls.json
curriculum/l2-uk-en/*/*/knowledge_packet.md

# Etymology data manifest is NOT gitignored — it's the build-time data source
# for the Astro dynamic route at starlight/src/pages/etymology/[slug].astro,
# consumed via getStaticPaths(). github.io's build runner has no access to
# data/sources.db (1.5 GB, not in repo), so the manifest must be checked in
# so the deploy pipeline can build pages from it. ~27 MB JSON, infrequent
# updates (ESUM volumes are a stable published reference work).
#
# Regenerate when ESUM data changes:
#   .venv/bin/python scripts/etymology/build_data_manifest.py
data/lexicon/slovnyk_cache/
# Network-fetch enrichment caches (Wikipedia summaries, GRAC frequency). Churny +
# growing toward the full-corpus target; like slovnyk_cache/ + the manifest they do
# NOT belong in git. Kept local + Drive-backed via scripts/backup-data.sh (rsyncs all
# of data/); CI never reads them (it hydrates the published release-asset manifest).
# Regenerate on demand via scripts/lexicon/enrich_manifest.py.
data/lexicon/cache/
# Generated build artifact: regenerate on demand with
#   .venv/bin/python -m scripts.lexicon.grow_lexicon_from_content (#3675 P2; promotion = P3)
data/lexicon/grow_candidates.json
data/lexicon/grow_needs_review.json
data/eval-archive/

# clawpatch tool output (config + findings + locks + patches — regenerable)
.clawpatch/

